This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kemod Cordaro Maclin appeared by video.  Attorney Michael J Cerniglia appeared by video for Kemod Cordaro Maclin.  Prosecuting attorney James C Griffin in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defense has received a global offer and discovery, requesting a solo offer on this case and jury trial dates. Case is adjourned in Branch 02.
Final pre-trial scheduled for December 2, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Jury trial scheduled for December 12, 2022 at 09:00 am.

JusticePoint Pretrial Services VIOLATION Report received and filed.  

Justice Point Pretrial Services Violation Report dated 8-29-2022; Received, filed and forwarded to the Judge for review.

Defendant Kemod Cordaro Maclin in court in person with Attorney Michael J Cerniglia who appears by video.  Katrina Amy Voge appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 02, Judge Childs. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 02.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Kemod Cordaro Maclin not in court, defendant in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness was present. Attorney Cerniglia to be appointed pending a conflict check. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 20, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  No driving without a valid license.

Defendant Kemod Cordaro Maclin in court with attorney Theodore OReilly.  Defendant Kemod Cordaro Maclin in custody.  Lisa M Valenti-Jordan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Kemod Cordaro Maclin appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL. Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count(s) 4 and 5. Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4). This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 23, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
